gomodel:SYNGO_39  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: deletion of SNAP-25 leads to strongly reduced neuron survival, and, in the few surviving cells, impaired arborization, reduced spontaneous release, and complete arrest of evoked release.. Experimental description: Results; \"To study the different functionality of SNAP-25 variants, we used Snap-25 null **mice** (Washbourne et al., 2002).\"\n\nAlthough SNAP25 is overexpressed, this is only to show that the effect of SNAP25 KO on SV release is really caused by loss of SNAP25.; the species of OE SNAP25 is irrelevant to the species determination therefore." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_39" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

